MMM - 04/07/2026 MMM - 04/07/2026
1 routine directory information specified and made public consistent with
2 20 U.S.C. 1232g, as such section existed on February 1, 2013, and
3 regulations adopted thereunder;
4 (2) Medical records, other than records of births and deaths and
5 except as provided in subdivisions (5) and (27) of this section, in any
6 form concerning any person; records of elections filed under section
7 44-2821; and patient safety work product under the Patient Safety
8 Improvement Act;
9 (3) Trade secrets, academic and scientific research work which is in
10 progress and unpublished, and other proprietary or commercial information
11 which if released would give advantage to business competitors and serve
12 no public purpose;
13 (4) Records which represent the work product of an attorney and the
14 public body involved which are related to preparation for litigation,
15 labor negotiations, or claims made by or against the public body or which
16 are confidential communications as defined in section 27-503;
17 (5) Records developed or received by law enforcement agencies and
18 other public bodies charged with duties of investigation or examination
19 of persons, institutions, or businesses, when the records constitute a
20 part of the examination, investigation, intelligence information,
21 complaints or inquiries from residents of this state or other interested
22 persons, informant identification, or strategic or tactical information
23 used in law enforcement training, except that this subdivision shall not
24 apply to records so developed or received:
25 (a) Relating to the presence of and amount or concentration of
26 alcohol or drugs in any body fluid of any person; or
27 (b) Relating to the cause of or circumstances surrounding the death
28 of an employee arising from or related to his or her employment if, after
29 an investigation is concluded, a family member of the deceased employee
30 makes a request for access to or copies of such records. This subdivision
31 does not require access to or copies of informant identification, the
-3-

