1 names or identifying information of members of the public making
2 complaints or inquiries, other information which would compromise an
3 ongoing criminal investigation, or information which may be withheld from
4 the public under another provision of law. For purposes of this
5 subdivision, family member means a spouse, child, parent, sibling,
6 grandchild, or grandparent by blood, marriage, or adoption;
7 (6) The identity and personal identifying information of an alleged
8 victim of sexual assault or sex trafficking as provided in section
9 29-4316;
10 (7) Appraisals or appraisal information and negotiation records
11 concerning the purchase or sale, by a public body, of any interest in
12 real or personal property, prior to completion of the purchase or sale;
13 (8) Personal information in records regarding personnel of public
14 bodies other than salaries and routine directory information;
15 (9) Information solely pertaining to protection of the security of
16 public property and persons on or within public property, such as
17 specific, unique vulnerability assessments or specific, unique response
18 plans, either of which is intended to prevent or mitigate criminal acts
19 the public disclosure of which would create a substantial likelihood of
20 endangering public safety or property; computer or communications network
21 schema, passwords, and user identification names; guard schedules; lock
22 combinations; or public utility infrastructure specifications or design
23 drawings the public disclosure of which would create a substantial
24 likelihood of endangering public safety or property, unless otherwise
25 provided by state or federal law;
26 (10)(a) Except as otherwise provided in this subdivision (10),
27 information (10) Information that relates details of physical and cyber
28 assets of critical energy infrastructure, critical water infrastructure,
29 critical telecommunications and broadband infrastructure, or critical
30 electric infrastructure, including (i) (a) specific engineering,
31 vulnerability, or detailed design information about proposed or existing
