1 critical energy infrastructure, critical water infrastructure, critical
2 telecommunications and broadband infrastructure, or critical electric
3 infrastructure that (A) (i) relates details about the production,
4 generation, transportation, transmission, or distribution of energy,
5 electronic data, or water, (B) (ii) could be useful to a person in
6 planning an attack on such critical infrastructure, and (C) (iii) does
7 not simply give the general location of the critical infrastructure and
8 (ii) (b) the identity of personnel whose primary job function makes such
9 personnel responsible for (A) (i) providing or granting individuals
10 access to physical or cyber assets or (B) (ii) operating and maintaining
11 physical or cyber assets, if a reasonable person, knowledgeable of the
12 electric, water, telecommunications and broadband, utility or energy
13 industry, would conclude that the public disclosure of such identity
14 could create a substantial likelihood of risk to such physical or cyber
15 assets.
16 (b) Subdivision (10)(a)(ii) (10)(b) of this section shall not apply
17 to the identity of a chief executive officer, general manager, vice
18 president, or board member of a public entity that manages critical
19 energy infrastructure, critical water infrastructure, critical
20 telecommunications and broadband infrastructure, or critical electric
21 infrastructure. The lawful custodian of the records must provide a
22 detailed job description for any personnel whose identity is withheld
23 pursuant to subdivision (10)(a)(ii) (10)(b) of this section.
24 (c) This subdivision (10) does not apply to the following
25 information regarding critical water infrastructure:
26 (i) Information relating to water quality, including consumer
27 confidence reports and sampling results, public notices of violations,
28 and compliance monitoring data;
29 (ii) Information relating to general descriptions of facilities,
30 projects, budgets, or maintenance activities that does not reveal
31 specific vulnerabilities; or
